  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will determine the efficacy of collagen cross linking for progressive keratoconus
      and ectasia after lasik. It will try and determine which is a more effective treatment:
      collagen cross linking alone or collagen cross linking combined with Intacs, a treatment
      which has already been proven to be effective in decreasing corneal curvature in patients
      with keratoconus.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
